metadata:
  section_id: 1
  section_name: Chapter 1
  hadith_first: 1
  hadith_last: 179

hadiths[179]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
1,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said regarding the sea,\n""It's water is purifying and its dead (animals) are lawful (to eat)."" \n\n",,,49118,"Narrated Abu Huraira:",Chapter 1
2,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Water is pure and nothing can make it impure”.\n\n",,,49119,"Narrated Narrated Abu Sa'id al-Khudri:",Chapter 1
3,"Narrated Abu Umama Al-Bahili:\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Water cannot be rendered impure by anything except something which changes its smell, taste and colour”. \n.",,,49120,"Narrated Abu Umama Al-Bahili:",Chapter 1
4,"“Water is pure unless any impure thing is added which changes its smell, taste and colour”.",,,49121,"And Al-Baihaqi reported:",Chapter 1
5,"Allah’s Mesenger (ﷺ) said:\n“If there is enough water to fill two pots (Qulla), it carries no impurity,” Another version has: “It does not become unclean”.\n{Al-Arba’a reported it. Ibn Khuzaima, Ibn Hibban and Al-Hakim graded it Sahih (sound)].",,,49122,"Narrated ‘Abdullah bin ‘Umar (rad):",Chapter 1
6,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said:\n“None of you should take a bath in stagnant water when he is sexually impure”. ",,,49123,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
7,"“None of you should urinate in stagnant water that is not flowing, and then take bath in it”.\nA version of Muslim has the words “from it (i.e. the water)”.\nA version of Abu Da’ud has: “One should not take bath in it from sexual impurity”.",,,49124,"Another version of Al-Bukhari has:",Chapter 1
8,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) forbade a women to bathe with the water left over by a man and that a man should not bathe with the water left over by a woman (but instead) they should both take scoopfuls of the water together. .,,,49125,"A man who accompanied the prophet (ﷺ) narrated:",Chapter 1
9,"Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas (rad):\nThe Prophet (ﷺ) used to bath with the water left over by Maimuna (rad) .",,,49126,"Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas (rad):",Chapter 1
10,"And Ashab As-Sunan (compilers of the prophet’s sayings) reported that one of the wives of the Prophet (ﷺ) took bath from a vessel, then came the Prophet (ﷺ) and when he wanted to take bath from that (vessel), she said, “I was sexually impure”. He said, “Water does not become sexually impure”. .",,,49127,,Chapter 1
11,"Narrated by Abu Huraira (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “The cleansing of the utensil belonging to one of you, after it has been licked by a dog, is to wash it seven times, and using soil for cleaning at the first time.” .",,,49128,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
12,“he should spill the content”.,,,49129,"Another version has:",Chapter 1
13,At-Tirmidhi’s version has “using soil at the first or last time”.,,,49130,,Chapter 1
14,"Narrated Abu Qatada (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said about the cat that, “It is not unclean, but is one of those who intermingle with you.” .",,,49131,"Narrated Abu Qatada (rad):",Chapter 1
15,"Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad): \nA Bedouin came and urinated in one corner of the mosque and the people shouted at him, but Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) stopped them, and when he finished urinating, the Prophet (ﷺ) ordered for a bucket of water which was spilt over it .",,,49132,"Narrated Anas bin Malik:",Chapter 1
16,"Narrated Ibn 'Umar (rad): \nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: ""Two types of dead animals and two types of bloods have been made lawful for us, the two types of dead animals are locusts and fish (seafood), while the two types of bloods are the liver and the spleen"". ",,,49133,"Narrated Ibn 'Umar:",Chapter 1
17,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When a fly falls in the drink of one of you, he should fully dip it and then throw it away because there is disease in one of its wings and cure in the other”. ",,,49134,"Narrated Abu Huraira:",Chapter 1
18,“It (the fly) protects itself with the diseased wing (by dipping it first in a drink).,,,49135,"and Abu Da’ud who added:",Chapter 1
19,"Narrated Abu Waqid Al-Laithi (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Whatever (portion) is cut off from an animal when it is alive is dead (meat). .",,,49136,"Narrated Abu Waqid Al-Laithi:",Chapter 1
20,"Narrated Hudhaifa bin Al-Yaman (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Do not drink in silver or gold utensils, and do not eat in plates of such metals, for such things are for them (the disbelievers) in this worldly life and for you in the Hereafter.” ",,,49137,"Narrated Hudhaifa bin Al-Yaman:",Chapter 1
21,"Narrated Umm Salama (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “He who drinks in a silver utensil is only swallowing Hell-fire in his stomach”. ",,,49138,"Narrated Umm Salama:",Chapter 1
22,"Narrated  (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: ""When the skin is tanned it becomes purified.” . Al-Arba’a have the words: ""Any skin that is tanned ... """,,,49139,"Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas:",Chapter 1
23,"Narrated  (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “The tanning of a dead animal’s skin purifies it”. .",,,49140,"Narrated Salama bin Al-Muhabbiq:",Chapter 1
24,"Narrated  (rad):\nSome people dragging a (dead) goat passed by the Prophet (ﷺ). He told them, “Had you better taken its skin”. They said, “It is dead”. He said, “Water and the leaves of the Acacia tree will purify it”. .",,,49141,"Narrated Maimuma:",Chapter 1
25,"Narrated  (rad):\nI said “O Allah’s Messenger! We are living in a land inhabited by the people of the Scriptures; can we take our meals in their utensils?” He said, “If you can get utensils other than theirs, do not eat in theirs, but if you cannot get other than theirs, wash them and eat in them” .",,,49142,"Narrated Abu Tha’laba Al-Khushni:",Chapter 1
26,The Prophet (ﷺ) and his Companions performed Wudu (ablution) from a skin water container belonging to a polytheist woman . (It is an extract of a long Hadith).,,,49143,"Narrated ‘Imran bin Hussain (rad):",Chapter 1
27,"Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad):\nWhen the cup of the Prophet (ﷺ) got broken, he fixed it with a silver wire at the crack .",,,49144,"Narrated Anas bin Malik:",Chapter 1
28,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) was asked about making vinegar out of wine. He said, “No (it is prohibited)”. .",,,49145,"Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad):",Chapter 1
29,"On the day of Khaibair, Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) commanded Abu Talha to announce: “Allah and His Messenger have prohibited for you (eating of) the flesh of the donkeys, for it is unclean”. .",,,49146,"Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad):",Chapter 1
30,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) delivered a Khutba (religious talk) to us at Mina while mounted on his camel and its saliva was pouring on my shoulders .,,,49147,"Narrated ‘Amr bin Kharija (rad):",Chapter 1
31,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to wash the semen and then go out for prayer in that (very) garment and I could still see the trace of the washing on it. ,,,49148,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):",Chapter 1
32,“I used to scrape it (the semen) off the garment of Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) and then he offered prayer with it.,,,49149,"In the version of Muslim:",Chapter 1
33,Verily! I (‘Aisha) used to scrape it (the semen) off his garment with my nails while it was dry.,,,49150,"In yet another version of Muslim:",Chapter 1
34,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “The urine of a baby girl should be washed off and the urine of baby boy should be sprinkled (with water)”. .",,,49151,"Narrated Abu As-Samh (rad):",Chapter 1
35,"The Prophet (Saw) said regarding menstruation blood that smears a garment, “She should scrape it, rub it with water, then wash it and then she may pray in it”. ",,,49152,"Narrated ‘Asma bint Abu Bakr (rad):",Chapter 1
36,"Khaula said, “O Messenger of Allah, suppose the (trace of) the blood does not go?” He said, “(Washing it with) water will suffice you and its trace won’t harm you”. .",,,49153,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
37,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said “Had I not feared burdening my Ummah, I would have commanded them to use Siwak with every ablution.” [Reported by Malik, Ahmad and An-Nasai. Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih (sound) and Al-Bukhari mentioned as a Mu’allaq (suspended – without its chain of narrators).",,,49154,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
38,"Uthman (rad) called for water to perform ablution. He washed palms of his hands three times, then rinsed his mouth and sniffed water in his nose and then blew it out. He then washed his face three times. Thereafter he washed his right hand up to his elbow three times, then the left one likewise, then he passed wet hands on his head. Then he washed his right foot up to the ankle three times, then the left one likewise. He then said, “I saw Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) performing ablution like this ablution of mine”. ",,,49155,"Narrated Humran, the manumitted slave of Uthman:",Chapter 1
39,He (the Prophet) wiped his head (with water) only once. .,,,49156,"Narrated ‘Ali (rad)  regarding the description of the ablution of the Prophet (ﷺ):",Chapter 1
40,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) wiped his head from the forehead to the back of his head and then back to the forehead with his (wet) hands. .,,,49157,"Narrated ‘Abdullah bin Zaid bin ‘Aasim (rad) describing the nature of ablution performance:",Chapter 1
41,"""He started with the front of his head, moved them (his hands) to the nape of his neck, and then returned them to the place where he started.""",,,49158,"In another narration by al-Bukhari and Muslim:",Chapter 1
42,"“Then he (Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ)) wiped his head, inserted his index finger in his ears and wiped the exterior of his ears with thumbs”. .",,,49159,"Narrated Abdullah bin ‘Amr (rad) regarding the description of the ablution:",Chapter 1
43,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When one of you wakes up from his sleep, he must blow of his nose three times, for the Satan spends the night inside one’s nostrils”  .",,,49160,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
44,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When one of you wakes up from his sleep, he must not put his hand in a utensil till he washed it three times, for he does not know where his hand was (while he slept)”.\n.",,,49161,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
45,"Allah’s Mesenger (ﷺ) said: “Perform a perfect Wudu run (your fingers) through the fingers of the hands and the toes, and if not fasting, sniff water up well inside the nose”. .",,,49162,"Narrated Laqit bin Sabra (rad):",Chapter 1
46,“If you perform ablution rinse your mouth”.,,,49163,"In another verson of Abu Da’ud is:",Chapter 1
47,"While performing Wudu, the Prophet (ﷺ) would run (his fingers) through his beard. .",,,49164,"Narrated ‘Uthman (rad):",Chapter 1
48,Two thirds of a Mudd (of water) was brought to he Prophet (ﷺ) (for ablution) so he began rubbing his arms. .,,,49165,"Narrated ‘Abdullah bin Zaid (rad):",Chapter 1
49,He saw the Prophet (ﷺ) taking some water to wipe his ears other than the water he had taken to wipe his head. .,,,49166,"Narrated ‘Abdullah bin Zaid (rad):",Chapter 1
50,"“he wiped his head taking extra water from that he had taken for the washing of the hands”, and this Hadith is Al-Mahfuz.",,,49167,"And the words of the Muslim version are:",Chapter 1
51,"I heard Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) saying, “My people will come on the Day of Resurrection with bright faces, hands and feet from the traces of Wudu. If any of you can lengthen his brightness, let him do so”. .",,,49168,"Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
52,"Allah’s Messenger (rad) loved to begin with the right while putting on his shoes, combing his hair, in his purification and in all his affairs .",,,49169,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):",Chapter 1
53,"Allah’s Messenger (rad) said: “When you perform ablution, begin with your right limbs”. .",,,49170,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
54,"The Prophet (ﷺ) performed ablution and passed wet hands on his forelock, over the turban and over the two leather socks. .",,,49171,"Narrated Al-Mughira bin Shu’ba (rad):",Chapter 1
55,"Regarding the Hajj of the Prophet (ﷺ): He said, “Begin with what Allah had begun with” .",,,49172,"Narrated Jabir bin ‘Abdullah (rad):",Chapter 1
56,The Prophet (ﷺ) used to run the water down his elbows while performing ablution .,,,49173,"Narrated Jabir bin ‘Abdullah (rad):",Chapter 1
57,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “There is no Wudu for one who does not mention Allah’s Name upon it. .",,,49174,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
58,At-Tirmidhi reported something similar to the above from Sa’id bin Zaid.,,,49175,,Chapter 1
59,and Abu Sa’id like this.,,,49176,,Chapter 1
60,and Ahmad said that nothing is authenticated in it.,,,49177,,Chapter 1
61,“I saw Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) rinsing his mouth and sniffing up and blowing his nose with separate scops of water.” .,,,49178,"Narrated Talha bin Musarrif, quoting his father on the authority of his grandfather:",Chapter 1
62,The Prophet (ﷺ) rinsed his mouth and sniffed and blew (his nose) with water three times. He sniffed up and blew his nose with the same hand from which he took the water. ,,,49179,"Narrated ‘Ali (rad) regarding performance of Wudu:",Chapter 1
63,The Prophet (ﷺ) put his hand (in the utensil) rinsed (his mouth) and sniffed up and blew (his nose) from one scoop (of water). He did that three times. .,,,49180,"Narrated ‘Abdullah bin Zaid (rad) regarding Wudu:",Chapter 1
64,"The Prophet (ﷺ) saw a man on whose foot appeared a portion like the size of a nail which was not touched by water. He then said, “Go back and perform your Wudu properly.” .",,,49181,"Narrated Anas (rad):",Chapter 1
65,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used only one Mudd of water for ablution and one Sa’ to five Mudd of water for his bath .,,,49182,"Narrated Anas (rad):",Chapter 1
66,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “If one after performing ablution completely recites the following supplication: (Ash-hadu an la ilaha ill-Allahu wahdahu la sharika lahu, wa ash hadu anna Muhammadan ‘abduhu wa Rasuluhu) ‘I testify that there is no one worthy of worship but Allah, He is Alone and has no partner and Muhammad (ﷺ) is his slave and Messenger’, all the eight gates of Paradise will be opened for him and he may enter through any gate he wishes”.",,,49183,"Narrated ‘Umar (rad):",Chapter 1
67,(Allahumma aj’alni minat-tawwabina waj’alni minAl-mutatahhirina) “Oh Allah! Include me among those who repent and those who keep themselves pure”.,,,49184,"Reported by Muslim and At-Tirmidhi who added the following words to the supplication:",Chapter 1
68,"Once I was in the company of the Prophet (ﷺ), he then performed ablution and I dashed to take off his socks. He said, “Leave them for I had put them on after performing ablution”. So he wiped over them .",,,49185,"Narrated Mughira bin Shu’ba (rad):",Chapter 1
69,"The Prophet (ﷺ) wiped over the upper part of the leather socks and the under part of it.\n.",,,49186,"Narrated by Al-Arba’a except An-Nasa’i:",Chapter 1
70,"If the religion were based on opinion, it would be more important to wipe over the under parts of the leather socks than the upper, but I have seen Allah’s Messenger  (rad) wiping over the upper parts of his leather socks. .",,,49187,"Narrated ‘Ali (rad):",Chapter 1
71,"When we were on a journey, the Prophet (ﷺ) used to command us to wear our leather socks for three days and three nights, whether we had to answer the call of nature or slept. However, in case of ejaculation or sexual impurity, he commanded us to remove the leather socks. .",,,49188,"Narrated Safwan bin ‘Assal (rad):",Chapter 1
72,The Prophet  (ﷺ) fixed the period of Mash (wiping) over the leather socks (Khifaf – plural of Khuff) for three days and nights for a traveller and one day and a night for the resident person in a town .,,,49189,"Narrated ‘Ali (rad):",Chapter 1
73,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) sent out a military expedition and commanded them to wipe over the turbans and leather socks. .,,,49190,"Narrated Thawban (rad):",Chapter 1
74,"“If one of you performs ablution and puts on his two leather socks, let him perform Mash (wipe) over them and pray in them and he may not take them off he so wishes except after ejaculation or sexual impurity. .",,,49191,"Narrated ‘Umar (rad), in a Mawquf (untraceable) and Anas in a Marfu (traceable) Hadith:",Chapter 1
75,"The Prophet (ﷺ) gave permission for the traveller to perform Mash (wiping) over his leather socks for three days and nights and for a non-traveller for a day and night, if he had put them on in a state of purity. .",,,49192,"Narrated Abu Bakra (rad):",Chapter 1
76,"I asked, “O Messenger of Allah, may I wipe over the Khuffain (leather socks)?” The Prophet (ﷺ) replied, “Yes”. I asked, “For one day?” He replied, “For one day”, I again asked, “And for two days?” He replied “For two day s too”. I again asked “And for three days” He replied, “Yes, as long as you wish”. ",,,49193,"Narrated Ubai bin ‘Imara (rad):",Chapter 1
77,"The Companions of Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) in his lifetime used to wait for the ‘Isha (night) prayer, so much so that their heads were lowered down  (by dozing). They would then pray without performing ablution. .",,,49194,"Narrated Anas (rad):",Chapter 1
78,Its origin is in Muslim.,,,49195,,Chapter 1
79,"Fatima bint Abu Hubaish came to the Prophet (ﷺ) and said, “O Messenger of Allah, I am a woman whose blood keeps flowing (even after the menstruation). I am never purified; should I, therefore, stop praying?” He (the Prophet) said: “No, for that is only a vein, and is not menstruation. So when the menstruation comes, abstain from prayers, and when it ends wash the blood from yourself and then pray”. .",,,49196,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):",Chapter 1
80,“Then perform ablution for every prayer”.,,,49197,"Al-Bukhari’s version adds:",Chapter 1
81,and Muslim admitted that he dropped this addition deliberately.,,,49198,,Chapter 1
82,"I was one who Madhi (urethral discharge) flowed readily and asked Miqdad (his slave) to ask the Prophet (ﷺ) about it. He (the Prophet) said:“One should perform Wudu (ablution) in this case”. .",,,49199,"Narrated ‘Ali bin Abi Talib (rad):",Chapter 1
83,The Prophet (ﷺ) kissed one of his wives and went to pray without performing (fresh) ablution. .,,,49200,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):",Chapter 1
84,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “If one of you feels disturbance in his stomach and doubts whether he has released some wind or not, then he should not leave the mosque unless he hears its sound or smells (its) odour”. .",,,49201,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
85,"A man said: “I touched my penis” or he said, “Does a man who touch his penis during the prayer should perform Wudu (ablution)?” The Prophet (ﷺ) replied, “No, it is only a part of your body”. [Reported by Al-Khamsa. Ibn Hibban graded it Sahih (sound).",,,49202,"Narrated Talq bin ‘Ali (rad):",Chapter 1
86,"and Ibn Al-Madini said, “It is better than the Hadith of Busra"".",,,49203,,Chapter 1
87,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “He who touches his penis should perform ablution”. [Reported by Al-Khamsa, and At-Tirmidhi and Ibn Hibban graded it Sahih (sound).",,,49204,"Narrated Busra bint Safwan (rad):",Chapter 1
88,"and Al-Bukhari said, “It is the most authentic in this chapter”.",,,49205,,Chapter 1
89,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Whoever vomits, bleeds through the nose, or released Madhi (urethral discharge) should go, perform ablution and then complete his Salat (prayer) (by continuing from where he had stopped at) on condition that he does not speak in the process”. \nReported by Ibn Majah",,,49206,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):",Chapter 1
90,and Ahmad and others graded it Da’if,,,49207,,Chapter 1
91,"A man asked the Prophet (ﷺ), “Should I perform ablution after eating mutton?” He replied, “If you wish so”, he then asked, “Should I perform ablution after eating camel meat?” He (ﷺ) said: “Yes”.\n.",,,49208,"Narrated Jabir bin Samura (rad):",Chapter 1
92,"The Prophet (ﷺ) said: “Whoever washes a dead person should take a bath (thereafter); and whoever carries it should perform ablution”. Reported by Ahmad, An-Nasa’i and At-Tirmidhi who graded it Hasan (fair).",,,49209,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
93,And Ahmad said that there is no authentic Hadith in this chapter.,,,49210,,Chapter 1
94,"The book written by Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) for ‘Amr bin Hazm also contained: “ None except a pure person should touch the Quran”. .",,,49211,"Narrated ‘Abdullah bin Abu Bakr (rad):",Chapter 1
95,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to mention Allah’s Name (praise Him) at all times.\n.",,,49212,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):",Chapter 1
96,The Prophet (ﷺ) had blood extracted from his body and offered the prayer and did not perform (a new) ablution. .,,,49213,"Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad):",Chapter 1
97,"Allah’s Messenger (saW) said: “The eye (when awake) is the string of the anus (to stop air escaping), and if the two eyes sleep the string is untied”. ”",,,49214,"Narrated Mu’awiyah (rad):",Chapter 1
98,"Also reported by Abu Da’ud mentioning the above addition without the words “the string is untied”, but both versions are weak.",,,49215,,Chapter 1
99,“Ablution is necessary for one who sleeps while he is lying flat. .,,,49216,"And Ibn ‘Abbas (rad) narrated in a Marfu’ (traceable) Hadith that:",Chapter 1
100,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Satan comes to one of you in Salat and blows air in his bottom, so he imagines that he has realised air yet he did not. So if he gets that feeling he should not leave his prayer unless he hears the sound (of the air) or smells its odour.” .",,,49217,"Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas (rad):",Chapter 1
101,It is originally from the Sahihain of Bukhari and Muslim as the Hadith narrated by ‘Abdullah bin Zaid.,,,49218,,Chapter 1
102,And Muslim reported by Abu Huraira likewise.,,,49219,,Chapter 1
103,"“If Satan comes to one of you and says: ‘You have nullified your ablution (by releasing air)’, let him say: ‘You have lied.” .",,,49220,"And Abu Sa’id narrated in Marfu’ Hadith:",Chapter 1
104,“Let him say in his heart...”,,,49221,"Ibn Hibban also reported the above Hadith with the version:",Chapter 1
105,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to remove his ring when entering the lavatory. .,,,49222,"Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad):",Chapter 1
106,"The  Prophet (ﷺ) on entering the lavatory used to say: \n\n“O Allah, I seek refuge with You from devils – males and females (or all offensive and wicked things, evil deeds and evil spirits, etc.)” ",,,49223,"Narrated Anas (rad):",Chapter 1
107,"Whenever Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) went to the privy, a servant and I used to carry a skin water container and a spear, and he would cleanse himself with the water. .",,,49224,"Narrated Anas (rad):",Chapter 1
108,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) told me, “Take the skin water”, he then went forward till he disappeared from me and relieved himself ",,,49225,"Narrated Al-Mughira bin Shu’ba (rad):",Chapter 1
109,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Safeguard yourselves from the two matters which cause accursing that befalls the one who relieves himself on people’s path-ways and under the shades.” .",,,49226,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
110,"He said: “Guard against the three things which cause curse (i.e.) defecating at the watering places, on the roadbeds and in the shades.” ",,,49227,"Narrated Mu’adh (rad):",Chapter 1
111,Ahmad reported from Ibn Abbas (rad) that defecation is prohibited also at the place where water collects. .,,,49228,,Chapter 1
112,"At-Tabarani also narrated on the authority of Ibn ‘Umar (with a weak chain of narrators), the prohibition of relieving oneself under fruit trees and beside the bank of a flowing river.",,,49229,,Chapter 1
113,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When two people go together to relieve themselves they should disappear from each other and do not talk, for Allah detests that”. .",,,49230,"Narrated Jabir (rad):",Chapter 1
114,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Nobody should touch his pennies with his right hand when urinating, and should not clean himself (from defecation or urine) using his right hand and should not breathe in the utensil (he is drinking from).” .",,,49231,"Narrated Abu Qatada (rad):",Chapter 1
115,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) forbade us to face the Qiblah when defecating or urinating, or to clean ourselves using the right hand, or to clean ourselves with less than three stones, or to clean ourselves with dung or a bone .",,,49232,"Narrated Salman (rad):",Chapter 1
116,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) “Neither face nor turn your back to the Qiblah while defecating or urinating, but turn towards the east or the west”. ",,,49233,"Narrated Abu Ayub (rad):",Chapter 1
117,"The Prophet (ﷺ) said: “If anyone goes to relive himself, he should conceal himself”. .",,,49234,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):",Chapter 1
118,"When the Prophet (ﷺ) came out of the privy, he used to say, “Ghufranaka (O Allah! Grant me Your forgiveness)”. .",,,49235,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):",Chapter 1
119,"The Prophet (ﷺ) went out to answer the call of nature and asked me to bring three stones. I found two stones and searched for the third but could not find it. So I took a dried piece of dung and brought it to him. He took the two stones and threw away the dung and said, “This is a filthy thing”. ",,,49236,"Narrated Ibn Mas’ud (rad):",Chapter 1
120,“Bring me more (something other than dung)”].,,,49237,"And in the version of Ahmad and Ad-Daraqutni it is added:",Chapter 1
121,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) forbade us to use a bone or dung for cleaning and said, “These two things do not purify”. .",,,49238,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
122,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Beware of (smearing yourselves with) urine, because it is the main cause of punishment in the grave”. ",,,49239,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
123,“Urination is the main cause of punishment in the grave”. .,,,49240,"and Al-Hakim reported that:",Chapter 1
124,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) educated us about lavatory (manners) that we should sit on our left foot and keep erect our right foot. .,,,49241,"Narrated Suraqa bin Malik (rad):",Chapter 1
125,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When one of you passes urine, he should empty his penis three times”. .",,,49242,"Narrated ‘Iesa bin Yazdad from his father (ra):",Chapter 1
126,"The Prophet  (ﷺ) asked the residents of Quba that what had earned them the Praise of Allah and they replied, “We use water after (cleaning ourselves with) stones.” ",,,49243,"Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas (ﷺ):",Chapter 1
127,and its Asl (original source) is in Abu Da’ud and At-Tirmidhi and Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih (sound) through Abu Huraira (rad) without mentioning the “stones”.],,,49244,,Chapter 1
128,"Allah’s Mesenger (ﷺ) said: “The water (of the ghusl) is due to the water (of sexual emission)”. ",,,49245,"Narrated Abu Sa’id Al-Khudri (rad):",Chapter 1
129,and its Asl (origin) is in Al-Bukhari.,,,49246,,Chapter 1
130,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said that, “If one of you sits between her legs (of a woman) and penetrates her, Ghusl (bath) is obligatory.” .",,,49247,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):",Chapter 1
131,“Even if he does not ejaculate”.,,,49248,"And Muslim added:",Chapter 1
132,"Umm Sulaim, the wife Abu Talha said, “O Allah’s Messenger! Allah is not ashamed of the truth. Is a Ghusl (bath) compulsory for a woman when she has a sexual dream?” He (ﷺ) replied, “Yes! When she sees signs of liquid” .",,,49249,"Narrated Umm Salam (rad):",Chapter 1
133,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said about the precept of a woman having ejaculation during sleep like a man, “She should take a Ghusl (bath)”. ",,,49250,"Narrated Anas (rad):",Chapter 1
134,"Umm Salama said, “Does this happen (to a woman)?” He (ﷺ) said: “Yes, otherwise where does the resemblance (of a child to its mother) come from?”",,,49251,"Added Muslim:",Chapter 1
135,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to take a bath from four things; after sexual intercourse, on Fridays, after extracting blood from his body and after washing a dead body. ",,,49252,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):",Chapter 1
136,The Prophet (ﷺ) ordered him to take a bath. ,,,49253,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad) regarding the story of Thumama bin Uthal when he embraced Islam:",Chapter 1
137,and its origin is in Al-Bukhari and Muslim.,,,49254,,Chapter 1
138,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Taking a bath on Friday is a must for every adult”. .",,,49255,"Narrated Abu Sa’id Al-Khudri (rad):",Chapter 1
139,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Whoever performs ablution on Friday has done a good thing and he who takes bath, taking bath is better  (for him).” ",,,49256,"Narrated Sumara (rad):",Chapter 1
140,The Prophet (ﷺ) used to teach us the Qur’an except when he was in a state of sexual impurity. .,,,49257,"Narrated ‘Ali (rad):",Chapter 1
141,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “If one of you has sexual intercourse with his wife and wishes to repeat he should perform ablution between them” .",,,49258,"Narrated Abu Sa’id Al-Khudri (rad):",Chapter 1
142,“Ablution makes one active for repeating (the sexual act).”,,,49259,"A-Hakim added:",Chapter 1
143,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to sleep in the state of sexual impurity without touching water. .,,,49260,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):",Chapter 1
144,"Whenever Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) took Ghusl (bath) after sexual intercourse, he would begin by washing his hands, then pour water with his right hand on his left hand and wash his sexual organ. He would then perform ablution, then take some water and run his fingers through the roots of the hair. Then he would pour three handfuls on his head, then pour water over the rest of his body and subsequently wash his feet. ",,,49261,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):",Chapter 1
145,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) poured water over his private parts and washed them with his left hand. He then struck his hand against the earth.,,,49262,"Narrated Maimuma (rad):",Chapter 1
146,"""And he wiped it with earth"".",,,49263,"Narrated Maimuna (Radhi Allahu Anhu):",Chapter 1
147,"And in the last of this version: “I handed him a piece of cloth, but he did not take it... He started shaking the water off his hand.”",,,49264,"Narrated Maimuna (Radhi Allahu Anhu):",Chapter 1
148,"I said, ""O Messenger of Allah, I am a woman who keeps her hair closely plaited. Do I have to undo them for Ghusl after sexual intercourse?"" In another narration, ""and after the end of menses?"" He replied (ﷺ), ""No, is it enough for you to throw three handfuls of water over your head.""\nRelated by Muslim.",,,49265,"Narrated Umm Salamah (RAA):",Chapter 1
149,"Allah's messenger (ﷺ) said: ""It is not permitted for a menstruating woman or one who is junub (sexually impure) to stay in the mosque.""\nRelated by Abu Dawud and Ibn Khuzaimah graded it as Sahih",,,49266,"Narrated `A'ishah (RAA):",Chapter 1
150,"I and Allah's Messenger (Peace be upon him) took a Ghusl (bath) due to sexual impurity from the same vessel and our hands alternated into it.\n\n\nIbn Hibban added ""and (our hands) met.""",,,49267,"Narrated `A'ishah (RAA):",Chapter 1
151,"Allah's Messenger (Peace be upon him) said: ""There is Janabah (trace of sexual impurity) under every hair, so wash your hair and cleanse the skin.""\nAbu Dawud and at-Tirmidhi transmitted it but they declared it to be weak.",,,49268,"Narrated Abu Hurairah (RAA):",Chapter 1
152,"Ahmad transmitted a similar narration to the above, on the authority of `A'ishah (RAA), but this version has an unknown transmitter.",,,49269,,Chapter 1
153,"The Prophet (ﷺ) said: ""I have been given five things which were not given to anyone else before me. Allah made me victorious by awe (of frightening my enemies) for a distance of one month's journey. The earth has been made for me (and my followers) a place for praying and something with which to perform Tayammum (to purify oneself for prayer). Therefore, anyone (of my followers) can pray (anywhere) and at any time that the Salat (prayer) is due.""",,,49270,"Narrated Jabir bin 'Abdullah (RAA):",Chapter 1
154,"""And the soil of the earth had been made for us as a means with which to purify ourselves (for prayer), when we cannot find water.""\nRelated by Muslim.",,,49271,"In another narration by Hudhaifah (RAA):",Chapter 1
155,"""The earth (dust) has been made for me as a means for purification.""",,,49272,"Ahmad transmitted on the authority of `Ali (RAA):",Chapter 1
156,"The Prophet (ﷺ) sent me on some errands and I became junub (sexually impure), and could not find water. I rolled myself in the dirt just as an animal does. I then came to the Prophet (ﷺ) and mentioned that to him. He said, ""This would have been enough for you,"" and he struck the earth with his hands once, then he wiped the right hand with the left one, and the outside of the palms of his hands and his face.\n.",,,49273,"Narrated `Ammar bin Yasir (RAA):",Chapter 1
157,"'He (ﷺ) struck the earth with the palms of his hands, blew in them and wiped his face and hands with them.",,,49274,"In a version by Al-Bukhari, `Ammar said:",Chapter 1
158,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: ""Tayammum is two strikes: one for the face and one for the hands up to the elbows.""\nReported by Ad-Daraqutni",,,49275,"Narrated Ibn `Umar (RAA):",Chapter 1
159,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: ""The soil is a purifier for a Muslim, even if he does not find water for ten years; but if he finds water, he must fear Allah and let it touch his skin.""",,,49276,"Narrated Abu Hurairah (RAA):",Chapter 1
160,a similar Hadith transmitted by at-Tirmidhi,,,49277,"Narrated Abu Dharr (RAA):",Chapter 1
161,"Two men set out on a journey and when the time of Salat (prayer) came they had no water. They performed Tayammum with clean earth and prayed. Later on they found water within the time of the prayer.  One of them repeated his prayer with ablution but the other did not repeat. Then they came to Allah's Messenger (ﷺ), and related the matter to him. Addressing himself to the one who did not repeat, he said, ""You followed the Sunnah and your (first) prayer was enough for you."" He said to the one who performed ablution and repeated: ""For you there is a double reward"".\n",,,49278,"Narrated Abu Sa'id al-Khudri (RAA):",Chapter 1
162,"concerning the verse, “And if you are ill or on a journey...” (an-Nisa': 43). He said, ""If a man sustains a wound, which he suffered during Jihad (in the cause of Allah) or ulcers, then he became junub (sexually impure) and is afraid that if he bathes he would die; he may perform ablution with clean earth (Tayammum).\n.",,,49279,"Narrated Ibn `Abbas (RAA):",Chapter 1
163,"One of my forearms was broken. Then I consulted Allah's Messenger (Peace be upon him) and he ordered me to wipe over the bandages.\n.",,,49280,"Narrated `Ali (RAA):",Chapter 1
164,"concerning the man who had a head injury, and then he made Ghusl and died: Allah's Messenger Peace be upon him said, ""It would have been enough for him to perform Tayammum and wrap it with something and wipe over the wrapping and wash the rest of his body.""\n",,,49281,"Narrated Jabir bin 'Abdullah (RAA):",Chapter 1
165,"It is from the Sunnah of the Prophet (ﷺ) for the man to pray only one prayer with each Tayammum, and then perform Tayammum for the next prayer.\n",,,49282,"Narrated Ibn `Abbas (RAA):",Chapter 1
166,"Fatima bint Abu Hubaish used to have a prolonged flow of blood (Istihadah) and so Allah’s Messenger (Peace be upon him)· told her, ""If it is the blood of menstruation it will be dark (almost black) and recognizable (by women). If it is that, then leave the prayer. If it is other than that, then make ablution and pray.""\n",,,49283,"Narrated `A'ishah (RAA):",Chapter 1
167,") ""She should sit in a tub, and if she sees yellowness appearing (on top of the water) she should wash (three times), once for the Dhuhr and Asr prayers, and once for the Maghrib and Isha prayers, and once for the Fajr prayer, and she should then perform ablution in between those times.""",,,49284,"In the narration of Asma bint ‘Umais, Abu Dawud transmitted, (the Prophet Peace be upon him said:",Chapter 1
168,"'I had a very strong prolonged flow of blood. I went to the Prophet (Peace be upon him) to ask him about it. He said, ""This is a strike from Satan. So observe your menses for six or seven days, then perform Ghusl until you see that you are clean. Pray for twenty-four or twenty-three nights and days and fast, and that will suffice you. Do so every month just as the other women menstruate  (and are purified).  But if you are strong enough to delay the Dhuhr prayer and advance the Asr prayer, then make Ghusl when your purified and combine the Dhuhr and the Asr prayers together; then delay the Maghrib prayer and advance the Isha prayer, and perform Ghusl and combine the two prayers, do so. Do so, and then wash at dawn and pray Fajr. This is how you may pray and fast if you have the ability to do so."" And he said, ""That is the more preferable way to me.""\n",,,49285,"Narrated Hamnah bint Jahsh:",Chapter 1
169,"Umm Habiba bint Jahsh complained to Allah's Messenger (Peace be upon him) about a prolonged flow of blood. He said to her, ""Keep away (from prayer) as long as your normal period used to prevent you (from praying), and afterwards she should perform Ghusl (and pray)"". (She used to take a bath for every prayer).\n",,,49286,"Narrated `A'ishah (RAA):",Chapter 1
170,"""And perform ablution for every Salat (prayer)"". Abu Dawud and others transmitted a similar narration.",,,49287,"In another version by Al-Bukhari, he (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 1
171,"After we were pure, we did not consider the yellow or muddy discharge to be anything (i.e. of the menses blood)\n.",,,49288,"Narrated Umm `Atiyah (RAA):",Chapter 1
172,"The Jews used not to eat with a woman during her menstruation period, so the Prophet (Peace be upon him) said: ""Do every thing else apart from sexual intercourse (with your wives)"".\n",,,49289,"Narrated Anas (RAA):",Chapter 1
173,"When I was menstruating, the Prophet saws would order me to wrap myself up (with an Izar, which is a dress worn below the waist) and would start fondling me.\nReported by Al-Bukhari and Muslim.",,,49290,"Narrated `A'ishah (RAA):",Chapter 1
174,"Allah's Messenger (Peace be upon him) said regarding a husband who has sexual intercourse with his wife during her menstruation period, ""He must pay a Dinar or half a Dinar in way of charity.”\n",,,49291,"Narrated Ibn `Abbas (RAA):",Chapter 1
175,"Allah's Messenger (Peace be upon him) said: ""Is it not the case that when a woman menstruates, she neither prays nor fasts?""\n",,,49292,"Narrated Abu Sa'id al-Khudri (RAA):",Chapter 1
176,"When we came to a place called Sarif, I menstruated and the Prophet (Peace be upon him) told me, ""You should perform all that a pilgrim would do, except circumambulation until you are pure (i.e. performed Ghusl).""\n",,,49293,"Narrated `A'ishah (RAA):",Chapter 1
177,"He asked the Prophet (Peace be upon him), “What is lawful for a man regarding his wife when she is menstruating?"" and he replied, ""What is above the waist wrapper (Izar).”\n",,,49294,"Narrated Mu'adh Ibn Jabal (RAA):",Chapter 1
178,"During the lifetime of the Prophet (Peace be upon him) the women having bleeding after delivery (postnatal or puerperal blood) would refrain (from prayer) for forty days.\n.",,,49295,"Narrated Umm Salamah (RAA):",Chapter 1
179,"""The Prophet (Peace be upon him) did not command her to repeat the prayers (missed during the period of bleeding).""",,,49296,"In another version of Abu Da’ud:",Chapter 1
